    ],
    "featureDescriptions": {
      "Skirmish": "Extra damage applies on attacks made during a round in which the scout moves at least 10 feet. The damage increases at 5th, 9th, 13th, and 17th level. The AC bonus begins at 3rd level and improves at 7th, 11th, 15th, and 19th level. Ranged skirmish attacks apply only within 30 feet. The ability does not function in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
      "Trapfinding": "A scout can use Search to locate traps with DCs higher than 20 and can use Disable Device to bypass or disarm magic traps.",
      "Battle Fortitude": "At 2nd level the scout gains a competence bonus on Fortitude saves and initiative checks. This increases to +2 at 11th level and +3 at 20th level. It is lost in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
      "Uncanny Dodge": "At 2nd level the scout cannot be caught flat-footed and reacts to danger before her senses would normally allow it.",
      "Fast Movement": "At 3rd level the scout gains a +10 foot enhancement bonus to base land speed. At 11th level this improves to +20 feet. It is lost in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
      "Trackless Step": "At 3rd level the scout cannot be tracked in natural surroundings.",
      "Bonus Feats": "At 4th level and every four levels thereafter, the scout gains a bonus feat from the scout bonus feat list and must meet its prerequisites.",
      "Evasion": "At 5th level the scout can avoid damage from certain attacks with a successful Reflex save.",
      "Flawless Stride": "At 6th level the scout moves through terrain that would normally slow movement at normal speed and without impairment, except for terrain requiring Climb or Swim checks or magically manipulated terrain. It is lost in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
      "Camouflage": "At 8th level the scout can use Hide in natural terrain. It is lost in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
      "Blindsense": "At 10th level the scout gains blindsense out to 30 feet.",
      "Hide in Plain Sight": "At 14th level the scout can use Hide in natural terrain even while observed. It is lost in medium or heavy armor or with a medium or heavy load.",
